name: CTFontManagerError
desc: Errors that prevent unregistration of fonts for a specified font file URL.

items.name: case fileNotFound
items.desc: An error that indicates the file doesn't exist at the specified URL.

items.name: case insufficientPermissions
items.desc: An error that indicates insufficient permissions to access the file.

items.name: case unrecognizedFormat
items.desc: An error that indicates the file's format is unrecognized or unsupported.

items.name: case invalidFontData
items.desc: An error that indicates the file contains invalid font data that could cause system problems.

items.name: case alreadyRegistered
items.desc: An error that indicates the file is already registered in the specified scope.

items.name: case exceededResourceLimit
items.desc: An error that indicates an operation failure due to a system limitation.

items.name: case assetNotFound
items.desc: An error that indicates the asset isn't found.

items.name: case notRegistered
items.desc: An error that indicates the file isn't registered in the specified scope.

items.name: case inUse
items.desc: An error that indicates the font file is actively in use and can't be unregistered.

items.name: case systemRequired
items.desc: An error that indicates the file is required by the system and can't be unregistered.

items.name: case registrationFailed
items.desc: An error that indicates the file can't be processed due to an unexpected FontProvider error.

items.name: case missingEntitlement
items.desc: An error that indicates the file can't be processed because the provider doesn't have a necessary entitlement.

items.name: case insufficientInfo
items.desc: An error that indicates the font descriptor doesn't have the necessary information to specify a font file.

items.name: case cancelledByUser
items.desc: An error that indicates the user cancelled the operation.

items.name: case duplicatedName
items.desc: An error that indicates the file can't register because of a duplicate font name.

items.name: case invalidFilePath
items.desc: An error that indicates the file isn't in an allowed location, which must be either in the app's bundle or an on-demand resource.

items.name: case unsupportedScope
items.desc: An error that indicates the specified scope isn't supported.
